1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:09,580
Okay, welcome back to Gary's Economics. Today is unfortunately my goodbye video for now because this will be the last video in the 24-25 season. Thank you.

2
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:17,500
Okay, so this is it. The last video while I go away. If you watch this, I'll probably already be in Italy.

3
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:24,020
I wanted to just talk. I've got here written on my script. Just run with no script, but I can't to be honest. I'm absolutely knackered.

4
00:00:24,020 --> 00:00:33,080
I want to talk a little bit about this season. And this season has been, I would say, probably the hardest season for me personally of Gary's Economics.

5
00:00:33,620 --> 00:00:37,820
If I'm honest, I think I probably exhausted myself a little bit in the first half of the year.

6
00:00:38,240 --> 00:00:45,519
It seems ages ago now, but the paperback came out in end of January. And the first half of the year was absolutely insane for me.

7
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:49,780
It was absolutely crazy. I was everywhere. It felt like I couldn't live my life, really.

8
00:00:49,780 --> 00:00:54,400
We were getting like 50 million views a month. It really felt like we were going to take the world over.

9
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:59,800
And I was working crazy, crazy, crazy, crazy hard. Really, really, really, really hard.

10
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:04,519
I didn't realise it was going to go on as long as it did. It just kept going and going and going.

11
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,920
And I had the holiday planned in the spring, which I kept postponing and postponing and postponing.

12
00:01:09,420 --> 00:01:14,440
And the holiday ended up being quite short. And I ended up working half the holiday and doing interviews all over the place.

13
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:21,580
And then when I came back in June to start this season, it really felt like we were kind of on the edge of winning World Tactics.

14
00:01:21,660 --> 00:01:26,900
And I really wanted to hit the ground running and really go. And I started making videos in June.

15
00:01:27,200 --> 00:01:32,820
And it was probably only about three or four videos in. I just started feeling like I was exhausted, to be honest.

16
00:01:33,180 --> 00:01:36,759
And I don't know if it was just me getting old or if I worked too hard.

17
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:41,760
But it was difficult for me because we'd achieved so much and we'd come so close.

18
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:46,420
It really felt like what it needed was for me to keep pushing and push more and more and more.

19
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:54,540
And it just felt like the legs weren't there, really. I didn't have the energy I needed to really run in.

20
00:01:54,840 --> 00:02:03,080
It felt like when I'm really doing a lot of work, I can be doing interviews and doing these videos and writing articles and appearing on people's podcasts.

21
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:06,980
And it really feels like you can kind of carry the thing on your back. But I couldn't, really.

22
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:15,880
This is the first time, really, that I've ever done this channel that I just felt like I didn't have the energy that I needed to push us to where we needed to be.

23
00:02:16,079 --> 00:02:21,579
And that was difficult for me, to be honest, especially because it felt like we were quite close to winning at times.

24
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:26,460
But I think if I'm honest, we were probably never that close yet.

25
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:33,600
And it's probably partially wishful thinking for me, in a way, because when you're working so, so, so hard, you just want to get there, right?

26
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:39,820
You want to get there. You want to reach the end. You want to win and have it won and kind of go away, go on holiday for like a year.

27
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:42,180
But the truth is, it was never going to be that easy.

28
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:46,500
We've made unbelievable, amazing, amazing strides this year to win the public.

29
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:49,540
But what we've seen is it's not enough just to win the public.

30
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:57,600
You do need to figure out how to win over the politicians, how to win over, you know, the media to some degree and this intellectual class.

31
00:02:57,700 --> 00:03:01,640
How do we break into that sort of, how do we break in with the posh people, basically?

32
00:03:01,859 --> 00:03:06,540
And I think the truth is we were never going to quite make it this year, which is a shame.

33
00:03:07,019 --> 00:03:09,579
But the truth is, it's exactly what I predicted.

34
00:03:09,959 --> 00:03:17,620
You know, if you go and if you go and look at the videos that we did just before the election, this is exactly what I said would happen.

35
00:03:17,620 --> 00:03:19,160
It's exactly what I said Labour would do.

36
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:21,940
Yeah, there's not a single thing that's happened that surprised me.

37
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:24,660
I didn't expect Labour to come over and they haven't.

38
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,840
I expected Labour to be unpopular and they have.

39
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,820
I expected Labour to change leader and it looks like they will.

40
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:32,340
A new leader will come in. It's a new opportunity.

41
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:34,540
But if I'm totally honest, I don't think we'll get them either.

42
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:42,120
But we are in a much, much, much stronger position than we were one year ago, two years ago, three years ago.

43
00:03:42,700 --> 00:03:45,080
The size of this movement, it's huge now.

44
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:47,560
So I'm going to keep fighting.

45
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:51,160
So that was kind of where I was when I came back and did the videos.

46
00:03:51,620 --> 00:03:56,580
I felt that my energy was kind of going, which is a shame because I'd only been back a sort of month, month and a half.

47
00:03:56,900 --> 00:04:02,440
And I always feel with these videos, I try my best to do them without a script, but it's hard when I'm tired.

48
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:11,240
And I feel like when you go without a script, what really drives the videos is your understanding and your passion and your energy.

49
00:04:11,240 --> 00:04:21,720
And it's sometimes difficult to combine those things because you want to keep that shape and structure and clarity you get from the understanding, but also allow that sort of passion to come through.

50
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:26,760
And what I felt really during this season was the energy was kind of going.

51
00:04:26,760 --> 00:04:37,420
And then we saw this massive, massive rise in the media salience of immigrant, refugee stuff, far right stuff.

52
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:48,120
And that was really difficult for me, to be honest, because, you know, I've always had this idea that I'm an economist and I talk about the economy.

53
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:52,900
And our current economic situation is not working or not going to work for 80, 90% of people.

54
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:57,300
So we can really rally and unite the public on this.

55
00:04:57,700 --> 00:05:03,600
And a big part of sort of the philosophy of this channel and my philosophy is basically about uniting the public.

56
00:05:04,460 --> 00:05:13,740
And as this anti-immigrant rhetoric really went up and up and up and up and up, what I probably felt most personally was just the division, basically.

57
00:05:13,940 --> 00:05:16,600
The division in the country, the division in the public.

58
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,960
And for me, it was difficult.

59
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:20,520
You know, I don't know people think I'm a communist.

60
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,480
I don't come from a political background.

61
00:05:22,900 --> 00:05:25,320
I come from a very working class, poor background.

62
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:29,000
But then I've been to fancy universities and I've worked fancy jobs.

63
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,960
So now in many ways, I'm in a more sort of middle class space.

64
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:46,080
And what I felt with this anti-immigrant thing reminded me a lot of how I felt with the Brexit thing, which was I saw the sort of class divisions in this society really being sort of torn at the seams.

65
00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:51,380
And it kind of felt like this division between the world that I came from and the world that I'm in now.

66
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,600
And it's hard, really.

67
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:53,520
It's hard.

68
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:58,760
It sort of, it breaks my heart in a way to see so much division.

69
00:05:58,760 --> 00:06:05,539
And I worry, I worry that if we don't do anything about this, we can end up kind of going the way that America has gone.

70
00:06:06,780 --> 00:06:12,000
Where basically the country is like split into two and everybody with a red hat hates everyone with a blue hat.

71
00:06:12,620 --> 00:06:15,400
And everyone with a blue hat hates everyone with a red hat.

72
00:06:15,620 --> 00:06:16,820
And I don't want it to go that way.

73
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:18,200
I don't want it to go that way.

74
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:26,180
So I decided to speak a little bit more about the protests and the migrant stuff, which is not something I'm super, super comfortable speaking about.

75
00:06:26,719 --> 00:06:28,099
But it felt like something I had to do.

76
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:32,960
And I did my best to speak about it in a way that is compassionate and understand what's happening.

77
00:06:33,340 --> 00:06:34,520
And I hope I said the right things.

78
00:06:34,980 --> 00:06:35,740
I do my best.

79
00:06:36,620 --> 00:06:38,260
But we've got to the end of the season now.

80
00:06:39,219 --> 00:06:40,640
I've been pushing it, if I'm honest.

81
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:47,719
Trying to sort of push myself to keep going because I was only away last in May, June.

82
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:49,479
And I felt bad to take another break.

83
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,580
But I could feel that exhaustion coming.

84
00:06:52,099 --> 00:06:57,800
And when I get to the end of a season, I kind of feel the same at the end of every season, really.

85
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:03,979
Which is this sense of having really worked a lot.

86
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:07,719
I put a lot of effort into this channel, into these videos.

87
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:10,060
And each season, we achieve more.

88
00:07:10,180 --> 00:07:11,340
And each season, we achieve more.

89
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:14,420
And this year in particular, I think it's amazing what we've achieved.

90
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,500
And you put so much work in and you get to the end.

91
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:20,760
And you realise that we still haven't won.

92
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:22,640
And we're not even winning.

93
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:25,280
And it's hard, I think.

94
00:07:25,640 --> 00:07:26,440
I find that hard.

95
00:07:27,020 --> 00:07:30,240
But what I want to say is, we are getting there.

96
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:32,040
We are moving forward.

97
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:37,480
The channel is like so, so much louder and bigger than it was.

98
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,580
When I started this channel five years ago.

99
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:46,080
I mean, when I started five years ago with my mate Simran, I never ever would have imagined that we can be what we are now.

100
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:50,980
Which is genuinely, legitimately, I think a major political player in this country.

101
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:52,000
That's what we are.

102
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,600
And that growth is thanks to you.

103
00:07:54,220 --> 00:08:16,180
This channel is ultimately a political experiment, which is to see whether an almost unfunded YouTube channel can compete with the major newspapers and political broadcasters, TV channels, radio channels, on the basis of word of mouth from the public.

104
00:08:16,180 --> 00:08:23,980
Just by being honest, being clear, being knowledgeable and explaining what's happening to the public.

105
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,500
And we're doing it.

106
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,120
We're doing it.

107
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:28,940
We're one of the major political players in the country.

108
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:31,220
And I'll keep doing it.

109
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,600
If we keep growing, we'll still be there.

110
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,380
There's big opportunities next year.

111
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:36,480
And I'll be back.

112
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:37,600
I'll do my best to take them.

113
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:41,620
Anyway, I want to thank Jack, cameraman.

114
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,900
Jack does great work.

115
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:47,100
These videos are a lot tighter when they go out than when I do them.

116
