259
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:26,420
We'd love to go and meet Gabriel Zuckman in France.

260
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:29,440
Jack's been practising his French, especially.

261
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:31,600
We don't know if we'll manage to figure that out.

262
00:16:33,260 --> 00:16:34,160
But I'll be back.

263
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:39,820
And in the meantime, keep watching the videos, keep making stuff, keep creating, keep talking

264
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:40,300
about it.

265
00:16:40,620 --> 00:16:41,500
The message is simple.

266
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,660
Living standards are falling because of growing wealth inequality.

267
00:16:44,660 --> 00:16:48,620
If you don't fix wealth inequality, if you don't fix the tax system, living standards

268
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:49,400
will fall further.

269
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:51,180
Tax wealth, not work.

270
00:16:52,719 --> 00:16:54,640
Yeah, keep fighting, keep talking about it.

271
00:16:54,699 --> 00:16:57,839
